      "text": [
        ": مَنْ قَرَأَ سَبِّحِ اسْمَ رَبِّکَ الْأَعْلَی فِی فَرِیضَهٍ أَوْ نَافِلَهٍ قِیلَ لَهُ یَوْمَ الْقِیَامَهِ ادْخُلِ الْجَنَّهَ مِنْ أَیِّ أَبْوَابِ الْجَنَّهِ شِئْتَ إِنْ شَاءَ اللَّهُ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.sayed-athar-husain-rizvi-&-sayed-maqsood-athar": [
          "1. From the previous chain from al-Hussain from his father from Abi Basir from Abi Abdillah (a.s.) who said: Whoever recites it in his obligatory and recommended prayers, it would be said to him on the Day of Judgment: Enter Paradise from whichever door you like."
        ]
      }
